<h1>Problem 907 - 1999 IMOSL, C6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Suppose that every integer has been given one of the colours red, blue, green or yellow. Let \(x\) and \(y\) be odd integers so that \(|x| \neq |y|\). Show that there are two integers of the same colour whose difference has one of the following values: \(x,y,x+y\) or \(x-y\).</p>
